pull_request.title: Enables CSS linting for improved code quality
pull_request.body:
This pull request introduces automated CSS linting to the project and improves the code quality workflow. The main changes include adding Stylelint configuration, updating the workflow to include CSS linting, and updating project scripts and dependencies.

**Workflow and Automation Improvements:**

* Renamed the GitHub Actions workflow from `Prettier Check` to `Code Quality Check` and updated the job name to `code-quality` for broader code quality coverage. (.github/workflows/prettier.yml)
* Added a new step to the workflow to run CSS linting using the `yarn lint` command, ensuring CSS code quality is checked on pull requests. (.github/workflows/prettier.yml)

**CSS Linting Integration:**

* Added a Stylelint configuration file (`.stylelintrc.json`) with recommended rules and customizations to enforce CSS best practices.
* Updated `package.json` to add `lint` and `lint:fix` scripts for running and auto-fixing Stylelint issues, and added Stylelint along with related configuration packages to `devDependencies`.Adds stylelint configuration and integrates it into the code quality workflow. This ensures consistent styling and helps catch potential CSS errors, improving the overall maintainability and quality of the codebase.

comment.body:


issue.title: Bypass sensor becomes unavailable.

labels.name: ramses_rf
labels.description: The issue is likely due to an underlying bug in the ramses_rf library.

issue.body:
**A big thank you!**
First of all, a big thank you to the new maintainers and the initial maintainer!

**Describe the bug**
The bypass sensor becomes unavailable after a few seconds with the new 0.51.0 version.

**To Reproduce**
Steps to reproduce the behaviour (for example):
1. Installed the new 0.51.0 version
2. Restarted Home Assistant
3. All sensor data seems to be present 
4. After a few seconds the bypass sensor becomes unavailable 
5. Restarted Home Assistant
6. Power down/up my Orcon unit
7. Power down/up my ESP32 connected to the CC1101
8. No dice
9. Installed version 0.50.1
10. Restarted Home Assistant
11. Bypass sensor data is present

Please provide code if you can. For example, if you are having an issue with a service call, provide a copy of the service call YAML/

**Expected behavior**
I expected the bypass sensor to behave normally using the new 0.51.0 version

**Please include the following information:**
 ```- ID
18:025584
Schema
{}
Config
enforce_known_list: true
Known list
- '18:025584':
class: gateway_interface
- '29:162275':
class: switch
faked: true
- '32:095506':
class: co2_sensor
- '32:139370':
class: ventilator
Block list
Is evofw3
true
```
 
 - contemporaneous portion of the **home-assistant.log**
 
```
No messages regarding this issue are logged in Home Assistant
```
 - contemporaneous portion of the **packet.log**
 ```
If necessary I can install the latest version to provide packet logs.
```

**Screenshots**
The only screenshot I can make is the bypass sensor with the unavailable status. Nothing more to see here.

**Additional context**
ESP32-S3 over Wi-Fi connected to EMQX MQTT server flashed with: https://github.com/IndaloTech/ramses_esp firmware.

issue.title: Fixed issues with streamlit 'rerun' attribute, placeholder and reset goal planner
issue.body:
## Which issue does this PR close?

This PR closes issues:
- #46 
- #47

## Rationale for this change

- #46 goal planner resets to older/preset values on clearing up and pressing enter which might lead the user to input wrong values if they haven't checked properly or constantly run into issues with old values popping up.
- #47 changed 'rerun' function with suitable version of streamlit.

## What changes are included in this PR?

- #47 changed `st.experimental_rerun()` to `st.rerun()`
- #46 added proper placeholders and logic.

## Are these changes tested?
Yes.
## Are there any user-facing changes?

No.

issue.title: [TF2] nav issues on Decoy, Coaltown (+ Ghost Town) and Mannworks (and fixes for them)
issue.body: i'm going to try and keep this relatively short and simple. affects Decoy, Coaltown, and Mannworks. mvm_decoy: - Fixed an issue where dropping the bomb near the spawn doors by the defender spawn would result in the robots being unable to pick up the bomb. (This one's been known about for a while, and was in the game since MVM launched. fixed by splitting the nav squares so that the door is a 6x2 square, and the rest is a 6x8 square.) mvm_coaltown & mvm_ghost_town: - Fixed an issue where robots would lose spawn protection uber before dropping down the rocky dropdown next to the Miner Barracks & Judgement Shed buildings. (An issue that's been in the map since it came out. also fixes being able to have the bomb drop up on the edge of the rock dropdown. ghost town has all the same nav issues coaltown does, so that's why it's included.) This one needs a screenshot with the nav disaplyed and the mesh decorations drawn to explain some additional context. the light blue squares are "Blue spawn exit", and as you can see, the edge of the rockface lacks those, and spawn protection uber is only granted to bots inside nav squares with the "Blue Spawn" or "Blue Spawn Exit" assigned to them. mvm_mannworks: - Attempted fix for the "Mannworks Shuffle" issue where bots would walk back and forth on the left and right spawnpoints for an extended period of time. - Also attempted fix for the bomb dropping through a staircase near the bridge with a fence next to it. ("Mannworks shuffle" is what's used to describe bots walking back and forth and stalling on diagonal dropdowns, since the issue originates in, well, Mannworks.) (this issue has been known, probably been in the game since MVM's launch, and while i can't replicate it in a local server, i've seen it happen a few times.) and here's fixes for these issues mentioned, these will not work on a local server unless you create a copy of these maps with a new name and name the nav files after said name (and keeping the .nav extension) if you want to test them out yourself. [MVM Decoy Coaltown Ghost Town Mannworks nav fixes.zip](https://github.com/user-attachments/files/21669709/MVM.Decoy.Coaltown.Ghost.Town.Mannworks.nav.fixes.zip)
